\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Without the friction term the motion occurs in 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(v,u\right)$
\end_inset

 along the contours of the constant energy density given by 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:energy_density_uv"

\end_inset

.
 For each value energy density these contours are plane algebraic curves
 - quartics.
 If we find an energy level completely enclosing the PD from the outside
 where 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{,X}>0$
\end_inset

 (so that in this model 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{,X}>0$
\end_inset

 too) the dynamical flow in an expanding universe will be directed to the
 interior phase space of this level of the energy density.
 Indeed, the normal to the 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon\left(v,u\right)=\varepsilon_{0}$
\end_inset

 contour is 
\begin_inset Formula $\overrightarrow{N}=\left(\varepsilon_{,v},\varepsilon_{,u}\right)$
\end_inset

, it points out outside of the closed contour, while the scalar product
 of a 
\begin_inset Formula $\overrightarrow{N}$
\end_inset

 with flow 
\begin_inset Formula $\overrightarrow{F}=\left(\dot{v},\dot{u}\right)$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\overrightarrow{F}\cdot\overrightarrow{N}=-\varepsilon_{,u}p_{,u}\sqrt{3G_{\text{N}}\varepsilon}=-2X\varepsilon_{,X}p_{,X}\sqrt{3G_{\text{N}}\varepsilon}\,.
\]

\end_inset

Any possible limit cycle will be located inside of the minimal energy density
 level 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{H}$
\end_inset

 enclosing the PD.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
The energy level 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{U}$
\end_inset

 touching the PD at the 
\begin_inset Formula $u-$
\end_inset

axes 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The curve of constant energy density 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\varepsilon\left(v,u\right)=\varepsilon_{U}=\varepsilon\left(0,1\right)=\Lambda+\frac{1}{12a}+\frac{1}{4}\,,\label{eq:E_U}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon\left(v,u\right)$
\end_inset

 is given by 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:energy_density_uv"

\end_inset

 touches the PD at 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(0,\pm1\right)$
\end_inset

.
 In the physical units, this energy density is given by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\varepsilon'_{U}=\Lambda'+\frac{1}{12a'}+\frac{1}{4}m^{4}=m^{4}\left(\Lambda+\frac{1}{12a}+\frac{1}{4}\right)\,.\label{eq:Physical_Energy_Density_Last}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

To avoid strong quantum gravity effects one has to require 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon'_{U}\ll M_{\text{Pl}}^{4}$
\end_inset

.
 For positive parameters this implies that 
\begin_inset Formula $m\ll M_{\text{Pl}}$
\end_inset

, and consequently the smallness of the dimensionless Newtons constant 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
G_{N}=\frac{m^{2}}{M_{\text{Pl}}^{2}}\ll1\,.
\]

\end_inset

Moreover, for the dimensionless parameter 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 we have the condition 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
a\gg\frac{m^{4}}{M_{\text{Pl}}^{4}}=G_{N}^{2}\,.
\]

\end_inset

For the pressure we have 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
p=2Xp_{,X}-\varepsilon_{U}\,.
\]

\end_inset

Now let us check when the energy level 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{U}$
\end_inset

, given by 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:E_U"

\end_inset

, can cross the PD somewhere else at a point 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{*}$
\end_inset

.
 We have 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\varepsilon\left(v_{*},\sqrt{1-3bv_{*}^{2}}\right)=\varepsilon_{U}\,,
\]

\end_inset

or 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{1}{4}\left(1-3bv_{*}^{2}\right)^{2}-\frac{1}{2}v_{*}^{2}+\frac{3a}{4}v_{*}^{4}=\frac{1}{4}\,,
\]

\end_inset

so that generically there is another root given by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
v_{*}^{2}=\frac{2}{3}\left(\frac{1+3b}{a+3b^{2}}\right)\,.
\]

\end_inset

However, the projection of the PD 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:NEC_ellipse"

\end_inset

 on 
\begin_inset Formula $v-$
\end_inset

axes only occupies 
\begin_inset Formula $v^{2}\leq1/3b$
\end_inset

 so that for 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
v_{*}^{2}>\frac{1}{3b}\,,
\]

\end_inset

the energy level 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{U}$
\end_inset

 does not cross the PD.
 Hence the condition for no crossing of the PD is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{2}{3}\left(\frac{1+3b}{a+3b^{2}}\right)>\frac{1}{3b}\,,
\]

\end_inset

or in other terms
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
3b^{2}-6b+a-2<0\,.\label{eq:no_second_touch}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

The roots of the left hand side of the last inequality are
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
b_{0\pm}=1\pm\sqrt{1+\frac{2-a}{3}}\,,
\]

\end_inset

so that there is no more crossings provided 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
1-\sqrt{\frac{5-a}{3}}<b<1+\sqrt{\frac{5-a}{3}}\,.\label{eq:condition_on_b_no_crossing}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

In particular, for 
\begin_inset Formula $a>5$
\end_inset

 there are no real roots 
\begin_inset Formula $b_{0}$
\end_inset

 of the left hand side of 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:no_second_touch"

\end_inset

 and the energy density level 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{U}$
\end_inset

 crosses the PD at four points 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(\pm v_{*},\pm\sqrt{1-3bv_{*}^{2}}\right)$
\end_inset

 after touching it at 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(0,\pm1\right)$
\end_inset

.
 Clearly, in that case, energy density level 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{U}$
\end_inset

 does not confine the PD.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Further, the energy level 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{U}$
\end_inset

 crosses the 
\begin_inset Formula $v-$
\end_inset

axes at 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{V}$
\end_inset

 given by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
v_{V}^{2}=\frac{1}{-1+\sqrt{1+3a}}\,.\label{eq:Ev_crossing_phi}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

This is outside of the projection of the PD if 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
v_{V}^{2}>\frac{1}{3b}\,,
\]

\end_inset

which translates into inequality 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
b>\frac{1}{3}\left(-1+\sqrt{1+3a}\right)=b_{out}\,.\label{eq:condition_on_b_outside}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

These conditions 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:condition_on_b_no_crossing"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:condition_on_b_outside"

\end_inset

