\begin_layout Standard
Now let us find for which rages of parameters the energy density level 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{S}$
\end_inset

 encloses the Singularity 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:Singularity_ellipse"

\end_inset

.
 Let us first find whether 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{S}$
\end_inset

 can cross the Singularity.
 We have 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\varepsilon\left(v_{sin},\sqrt{\frac{1}{3}-bv_{sin}^{2}}\right)=\varepsilon_{s}\,,
\]

\end_inset

which yields 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
v_{sin}^{2}=\frac{2b-b^{2}-a}{3b\left(a-b^{2}\right)}\,.
\]

\end_inset

This crossing of the Singularity does not happen provided either when 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{sin}^{2}<0$
\end_inset

 i.e when 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
b\leq1 & \text{and} & a<b^{2}\,,\label{eq:v_sing_imaginary_1}\\
b\leq1 & \text{and} & a>2b-b^{2}\,,\label{eq:v_sing_imaginary_2}\\
b>1 & \text{and} & a>b^{2}\,,\label{eq:v_sing_imaginary_3}\\
b>1 & \text{and} & a<2b-b^{2}\,,\label{eq:v_sing_imaginary_4}
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset

or when 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{sin}^{2}>\left(3b\right)^{-1}$
\end_inset

 i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
b<1 & \text{and} & b^{2}<a<b\,,\\
b>1 & \text{and} & b<a<b^{2}\,.
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

On the other hand, as we discussed before, if we require a double crossing
 of the 
\begin_inset Formula $u-$
\end_inset

axes (so that 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{S}$
\end_inset

 consists of one piece) we have to demand that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
a>2b\,.
\]

\end_inset

We should also require that 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{S}$
\end_inset

 crosses the 
\begin_inset Formula $u-$
\end_inset

axes at 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
u_{S+}^{2}=\frac{b+\sqrt{b^{2}-2b+a}}{3b}>\frac{1}{3}\,,
\]

\end_inset

which gives 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
b\leq2 & \text{and} & a>2b-b^{2}\,,\\
b>2 & \text{and} & a>0\,.
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

 
\end_layout

